title Helper agent routing by trust class and risk boundary

participantspacing equal

actor User
control "Agent\nArchitect" as AA
control "Artifact-Trusted\nRole" as Trusted
control Explore
control "Undo-Safe\nDefault" as Undo

note over AA: Prefer explicit bounded agents over opaque helpers.
note over AA: Built-in default is an exception, not the baseline.

User->AA: task request
AA->AA: assess required boundary

alt explicit bounded role already exists
  AA->Trusted: use repo-defined role
  Trusted-->AA: bounded result
  AA-->User: artifact-backed outcome
else task is read-only
  AA->Explore: inspect, search, cross-check
  Explore-->AA: read-only evidence or uncertainty
  AA-->User: bounded read-only result
else task needs IDE-confined mutation only
  AA->Undo: mutate inside editor only
  Undo-->AA: undo-safe result
  AA-->User: IDE-confined mutation outcome
else task needs terminal, external effects, or specialized capability
  note over AA: Do not route this to Undo.
  AA-->User: justify stronger explicit agent
  note over AA: Use built-in default only if no explicit bounded agent can cover the need.
end